{{Tanakh OT}} The '''historical books''' are a division in the [[Christianity|Christian]] [[Old Testament]], corresponding to the [[Nevi'im#Former Prophets|Former Prophets]] of the [[Tanakh|Hebrew]] [[Nevi'im]] and two of the ungrouped books of [[Ketuvim]], together with the [[Book of Ruth]] (between [[Book of Judges|Judges]] and [[Books of Samuel|Samuel]]) and the [[Book of Esther]] (after [[Book of Nehemiah|Nehemiah]]) which in the [[Tanakh]] are both found in the [[Five Megillot]].
The historical books of the main Christian canons are as follows:
* [[Book of Joshua|Joshua]] * [[Book of Judges|Judges]] * [[Book of Ruth|Ruth]] * [[Books of Samuel|Samuel]] * [[Books of Kings|Kings]] * [[Books of Chronicles|Chronicles]] * [[Book of Ezra|Ezra]] (1 Esdras) * [[Book of Nehemiah|Nehemiah]] (2 Esdras) **[[Book of Tobit|Tobit]] (Catholic and Orthodox) **[[Book of Judith|Judith]] (Catholic and Orthodox) * [[Book of Esther|Esther]] ** [[1 Maccabees]] (Catholic and Orthodox) ** [[2 Maccabees]] (Catholic and Orthodox) ***[[3 Maccabees]] (Orthodox) ***[[3 Esdras]] (Russian and Georgian) ***[[4 Maccabees]] (Georgian)
